<span id="freeTextContainer14558731768846276156">To sum this up concisely: too much chest heaving, not enough character focus. I tried reading it, but got fed up with Alice&apos;s &quot;innocence&quot; and &quot;purity&quot; by first third of this book. In addition, I found it extremely unrealistic that Alice&apos;s view on Lucien changed so quickly from the scene where he forces her to make a decision between her or her sister in law staying and the next few scenes. Overall, just kind of terribly cheesy and dreadfully boring.</span>
  <span id="freeText14558731768846276156" style="display:none">To sum this up concisely: too much chest heaving, not enough character focus. I tried reading it, but got fed up with Alice's "innocence" and "purity" by first third of this book. In addition, I found it extremely unrealistic that Alice's view on Lucien changed so quickly from the scene where he forces her to make a decision between her or her sister in law staying and the next few scenes. Overall, just kind of terribly cheesy and dreadfully boring.</span>
