    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1900528491" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1900528491" />
    <a title="Sarah Z" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/53518683-sarah-z"><img alt="Sarah Z" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1460055379p2/53518683.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1900528491?book_show_action=true">Feb 06, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sarah Z" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sarah Z" href="/user/show/53518683-sarah-z">Sarah Z</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1900528491" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12446503820098476276">2.5 stars. I was going to rate it 3 because I liked the beginning so much, but overall it was just so bad. Such a pity because I really liked her writing, but the story was awful.<br/><br/>Let me start by saying how amazing the start of the book was! I was like wow this is good. This is going to be awesome. I actually found myself more in love with Damien at first haha, but Lucien was dark and rakish and he intrigued me. Then we shift to Alice and I adored her. I couldn&apos;t wait for her to change Lucien&apos;s b</span>
  <span id="freeText12446503820098476276" style="display:none">2.5 stars. I was going to rate it 3 because I liked the beginning so much, but overall it was just so bad. Such a pity because I really liked her writing, but the story was awful.<br /><br />Let me start by saying how amazing the start of the book was! I was like wow this is good. This is going to be awesome. I actually found myself more in love with Damien at first haha, but Lucien was dark and rakish and he intrigued me. Then we shift to Alice and I adored her. I couldn't wait for her to change Lucien's bad boy ways. She goes to Lucien's house to chase after her sister-in-law and finds herself at a cult party/orgy. I'm like what?!?!? This is getting intense! Crazy and different, but in a good way. Alice meets Lucien, there is some great chemistry. Enter Caro (sister-in-law), hilarity ensues. But then...... all hell breaks loose. <br /><br />So Lucien holds Alice hostage for a week and Caro heads home. I didn't mind it, I just thought it was dumb. Then, the leads do a 180. Lucien is not quite a rogue anymore. I'm like wait, what just happened? He hardly knows Alice. Okay, she's attractive and a virgin. I guess there was a shortage of attractive virgins in those days? And not only was she a virgin, but she was nice! So crazy! So after knowing each other for 4 days I believe, they were in love (cue eye roll emoji). I'm still wondering what about her he fell in love with? I'm sorry but this is insta-lust, not love. Like I mentioned above, Alice did a 180 also. All of a sudden, I couldn't stand her. She supposedly fell in love in 4 days and then Miss-Goody-Two-Shoes virgin gave up her virginity. It's like a bad movie. Guy tells a woman he's in love, gets in her pants, moves onto the next. Oh but I forgot, Lucien is for reasons unbeknownst to me, in love.<br /><br />But I can't quite stop there because Alice's character just gets worse. So they love each other, yet when he asks her to stay put, she follows him and discovers he's a spy. In my book, you tell someone you love them, you trust them. That goes both ways. Alice couldn't trust him and stay in her room, he couldn't trust telling her he's a spy. Well he finally comes clean and Alice who is TSTL, over and over again, she gives him an ultimatum and he chooses his arch nemesis over her. She leaves, and her week with Lucien is over. But wait, there's about a million more pages and I'm ready to start skimming.<br /><br />I don't really feel like continuing the summary, but it just gets so over the top. Parts were way too corny, way too slow, and getting rid of Bardou drags on and on and on. Ugh. I was sad at first that I didn't start the series in order (I usually try to do that), but now I'm pretty happy I didn't because I don't know if I can read any more of her books. It's a shame, Foley started out with a bang and blew it for me. I like her writing enough to maybe try one more, but I don't have high hopes..</span>
  <a data-text-id="12446503820098476276" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


